
[1]secularize

   SEC'ULARIZE, v. t.

   1. To make secular; to convert from spiritual appropriation to scular
   or common use; to convert that which is regular or monastic into
   secular; as, the ancient regular cathedral churches were secularized.

   At the reformation, the abbey was secularized. Coxe, Switz.

   2. To make worldy.
